New Records: Spencer Strider achieved his major league-leading 17th win.
Atlanta Braves clinched their sixth consecutive NL East title.
Atlanta Braves achieved their 26th division title, a record in MLB history.
Austin Riley became the third Braves player to reach 35 homers in a season, tying the MLB record for most players with 35 homers on one team in a season.
Key Match Events: Austin Riley hit a two-run homer in the first inning.
Kevin Pillar hit an RBI double in the fourth inning.
Spencer Strider struck out nine batters, boosting his MLB-best total to 259.
Yates struck out Brandon Marsh to end the game.
Cristopher Sánchez struck out a career-best 10 in 7 1/3 innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Spencer Strider commented, 'Now the real party starts.'
Manager Brian Snitker said, 'We’ve checked one box.'
Phillies slugger Kyle Schwarber stated, 'The focus is on us, still. We’re going to keep pushing until the very end.'
Phillies manager Rob Thomson said, 'This group has been resilient all year.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves clinched the title on the same field where the Phillies eliminated them last October in the NL Division Series.
The Braves are tied for most players with 35 homers in a season on one team in MLB history.
Phillies manager Rob Thomson mentioned it would be a 'pleasant surprise' if injured first baseman Rhys Hoskins could return in the postseason.
